oxen-libquic (1.0.0-3~deb11) bullseye; urgency=medium

  * Bump static gnutls build version to latest release
  * Log level tweaks
  * Add a compile-time failure if not providing TLS creds to connect(...)
  * Disable log statement about no early data
  * Add configurable idle timeout; change default to 30s
  * BTRequestStream: fire pending callbacks as timeouts when closing
  * Make oxen/quic/version.hpp header less annoying
  * Allow individual handshake timeouts on connections
  * Increase default handshake timeout to 10s
  * Fix use-after-move
  * BTRequestStream: don't invoke close callback if there isn't one
  * Fix return for unfound replies/errors
  * Remove from sent_reqs before invoking the callback
  * Fix log message in handshake timeout case
  * Make sure buf is cleared after we process it
  * Downgrade log statement for normal use
  * macos sucks
  * Add warning when respond can't respond
  * Fix connection dropping during packet processing
  * Add remote address to unexpected packet warning
  * Shrink buffer to ngtcp2-returned size
  * tiny optimization: don't go through call_get
  * Privatize Endpoint
  * Defer public connection closing via call_soon
  * Add closing period for connections
  * Drop 0RTT
  * Allow providing an Endpoint static secret
  * Throw if we listen() multiple times & call_get
  * Properly detect incoming local address
  * Set packet source address when appropriate
  * Trash fix for trash OS
  * Trash fixes for the other trash OS
  * De-hang tests; de-bool promises; macro require_future
  * More apple defective OS workarounds
  * Fix ECN support
  * Fix log source root overwrite
  * Windows compilation fix
  * Longer timeout for ARM failures
  * Add Debian 11 sendmsg jobs
  * Zero control data
  * Make IPV6_RECVPKTINFO work on Windows

